defs.docs:
This crates provides data types to build structures ready to upload into UBO.
 Data layout will match one for uniform blocks declared with `layout(std140)`.
 See [specs](https://www.khronos.org/registry/OpenGL/specs/gl/glspec45.core.pdf#page=159) for alignment rules.

defs.name: Element
defs.docs:
Aligning wrapper.
 Elements for array are aligned to 16 bytes (size of vec4) at least.

defs.name: Array
defs.docs:
Array of `Element`s.
 This type implements useful traits for converting from unwrapped types.

defs.name: Uniform
defs.docs:
Structure to transform data from rust's structure to the raw data ready to upload to UBO.
 Users should prepfer to use `derive(Uniform)` instead of implementing this manually.
